nagement and profitability; agile test and learn marketing; customer lifetime management and portfolio optimization. Financial Develop and manage all marketing programs. Regularly share findings and identify campaign optimization opportunities to fulfill key growth, marketing allowable (profitability) and efficiency goals. Oversee expenses to ensure effective utilization of marketing, enablement and project spends, ensuring that appropriate tracking and benefit realization is managed. Enforce standards related to meeting budget commitments, marketing efficiencies and related marketing benchmarks. Good knowledge of financial aspects of digital, direct and partner marketing campaign management, including budgeting, revenue generation, direct and indirect expenses. Work closely with internal business units to ensure DDM strategy is aligned with all product and country strategies and are in compliance with prevailing governance standards. Campaign Management Own the achievement of acquisition, cross-sell and retention business targets and agreed KPIs. Create, manage, and implement integrated marketing campaigns and be the digital practice leader for Singapore. Leverage demand and agile marketing best practices and tools to attract, target, convert and retain customers through customer value management, compelling value proposition deployment, multi-channel marketing and test and learn methodologies. Ensure governance standards for campaign, marketing and telesales operations are well-managed. Manage and inspire external partners in the development and optimization of initiatives. Work closely with peer functions such as Product, Agency, Call Center and Marketing & Communications to amplify marketing efforts to pursue business goals. Actively lead and participate annual planning to ensure clear annual plans tied to country and business growth and profitability targets. Ensure the management of the end-to-end marketing discipline that leverages insights, data & analytics, processes and technology practices to maximize the effectiveness and efficiency of digital marketing initiatives. Constantly pursue marketing opportunities through effective leverage of customer insights, customer feedback mechanisms, digital tools, data and analytics to heighten digital customer experience and financial goals. Prepare and manage regular management reports for production metrics, customer experience and analytics. Manage and reconcile marketing budgets in tandem with peer business functions. Digital Enablement Develop and take ownership of Digital Enablement Strategy in concert with country financial and customer centricity goals, in the context of the five objectives for AIGSA, to support the distribution of products and services. Apply disciplined project management skills to manage digital enablement initiatives. Collaborate with country and regional teams to enhance digital marketing tools and capabilities. Develop and execute enablement strategies encompassing market segmentation, digital experience, product mix and positioning, channel optimization and efficiency and analytics to achieve or exceed defined business goals. Insight driven performance Establish and monitor industry level benchmarks for marketing performance and digital customer/partner experience. Develop competitive analysis by segment, channel and LOB - through a structured approach to identify and act on developments in the digital domain to defend and expand AIG\u2019 position in the market. Develop, manage and execute against a performance and productivity driven annual plan. Leadership Lead a multi-disciplinary team of professionals across marketing, analytics, sales operations and enablement. Build a performance-driven, test and learn and commercially-driven team focused on performance and productivity, Champion a culture of proactively managing risk, continuous improvement, action and accountability. TECHNICAL SKILLS & EXPERTISE 10-15 years\u2019 work experience with extensive understanding of Direct and Digital Marketing campaign and financial management, analysis and profitability performance reporting. Outstanding skills in commercial strategy development and execution across channels and platforms. Experienced in the management of integrated/multi-channel marketing and cross-discipline marketing concepts from creation to implementation. Excellent Project Management skills and demonstrated ability to function as a digital leader within a cross-functional organization. Demonstrated ability to adapt digital marketing tactics in response to technology developments as they arise. Solid understanding of the marketing landscape including web, mobile, content management, video, voice, tools and advertising. Strong interest in digital marketing, data analytics and data-driven business performance management. Highly developed analytical, communication and presentation skills, interpersonal skills and the ability to work with technical and non-technical business groups across the organization. High degree of professional confidence and credibility with effective presence, strong written and verbal communication skills, able to communicate concepts and plans that resonates with internal target audience at all levels. Excellent business analysis ability.Good working knowledge managing financial aspects of the business including budgeting, sales revenue, direct and indirect expenses and portfolio/remediation management. Mature and proven track record in working independently and collaboratively with minimal guidance. An outcome-driven, creative thinker with an innovative bent to problem solving. Strong knowledge of competitor or \u201cbest in class\u201d functionality and a keen ability to prioritize tasks to deliver quick yet meaningful results. Insurance and/or financial institution experience highly desired. It has been and will continue to be the policy of American International Group, Inc., its subsidiaries and affiliates to be an Equal 